                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12472: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-09-26T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 26, 1933—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 26—4:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>770. Legation’s 753, September 18, 11 a.m. Following from American Consul at
                    Foochow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“September 25, 11 a.m. My September 15, 3 p.m. American Dominican
                            Procuration reports that Padres Curran, Werner, and Grace have arrived
                            safely at Hangchow, Chekiang.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
